<P>AN ACCOUNT OF THE <HI>RISE</HI> and <HI>PROGRESS</HI> OF THE Beech-Oil Invention, AND All the Steps which have been taken in that Affair, from the Fir&s;t Di&s;covery, to the pre&s;ent Time.</P>
<P>AS ALSO, What is further de&s;ign'd in That Undertaking.</P>
<Q><P>How long, ye &s;imple Ones, will ye love Simplicity? How long, O ye Scorners, will you delight in your Scorning? And Fools hate Knowledge?</P>
<BIBL><HI>Prov.</HI></BIBL></Q>
<P>By <HI>AARON HILL</HI> <ABBR>E&s;q</ABBR></P>
<P>LONDON, Printed in the Year MDCCXV.</P>
</DIV1>
