<SALUTE><HI>SIR,</HI></SALUTE></OPENER>
<P><Q>&startq;HAving cro&s;s'd the <HI>Appennine</HI> Mountains, I am &s;afe at this Place, and ob&s;erve, as I go on, that the Drawers of Rape-Oil are the only Enemies to your Invention, e&s;pecially one <HI>Beaver</HI> of <HI>Wakefield</HI>, who keeps 8 or 10 Mills at work the Year round. Their Oil, upon my coming, is fallen to two Shillings and four Pence, and <HI>Seville</HI> Oil to four Shillings <HI>per</HI> Gallon. The Soap-makers in my Travels wanting Oil, make a &s;ort of hard Soap of Tallow. The Leather-dre&s;&s;ers are few, &endq;and u&s;e Fi&s;h-Oil only.</Q></P>
